---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="How It Works" description="Fund. Deploy. Train. Measure. See how Restore the Last delivers nervous system restoration to those who need it most.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-deep text-white section-padding">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <p class="label text-gold mb-4">How It Works</p>
      <div class="gold-line mb-8"></div>
      <h1 class="text-white text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif font-bold leading-tight max-w-3xl">
        Four steps between funded and healed.
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Expanded Model -->
  <section class="bg-offwhite section-padding">
    <div class="container-narrow max-w-4xl">
      <div class="space-y-16">

        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[120px_1fr] gap-8 items-start">
          <div>
            <p class="label text-gold text-lg">Step 01</p>
            <p class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-primary">Fund</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl mb-4">Donors choose real projects.</h3>
            <p class="text-body leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Every dollar funds a specific deployment. You choose a partner facility, a population, a country. You know where your money goes before it leaves your account.
            </p>
            <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
              No general fund. No administrative mystery. Project-based giving — the model that built Charity: Water and changed how people think about donating.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="border-primary/10">

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[120px_1fr] gap-8 items-start">
          <div>
            <p class="label text-gold text-lg">Step 02</p>
            <p class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-primary">Deploy</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl mb-4">Technology placed on-site.</h3>
            <p class="text-body leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We deliver direct neurofeedback equipment directly to partner facilities — children's homes, residential campuses, recovery centers. On-site placement means residents don't need referrals. They walk down the hall.
            </p>
            <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
              On-campus delivery is more effective than clinic referral. It's safer, more consistent, and dramatically increases participation.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="border-primary/10">

        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[120px_1fr] gap-8 items-start">
          <div>
            <p class="label text-gold text-lg">Step 03</p>
            <p class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-primary">Train</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl mb-4">Staff trained to deliver sessions.</h3>
            <p class="text-body leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Every deployment includes training for on-site staff. The goal is independence — partner facilities run their own programs, on their own schedule, with their own people.
            </p>
            <p class="text-body leading-relaxed mb-6">
              One trained practitioner can serve 160–200 clients per year to completion. A single machine with a part-time operator can transform a facility.
            </p>
            <img
              src="/8a4c65e8-7414-466c-852c-27cbadecc7ee.JPG"
              alt="Practitioner administering neurofeedback session to a child at ONUVA"
              class="rounded-lg shadow-md w-full max-w-sm object-cover"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="border-primary/10">

        <!-- Step 4 -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[120px_1fr] gap-8 items-start">
          <div>
            <p class="label text-gold text-lg">Step 04</p>
            <p class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-primary">Measure</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl mb-4">Every session tracked. Every outcome reported.</h3>
            <p class="text-body leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We don't guess at impact. Symptom severity is measured before, during, and after treatment. Donors receive outcome reports tied to their specific project.
            </p>
            <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
              Domains tracked include anxiety, insomnia, anger, depression, and physical complaints. This isn't anecdotal. It's clinical-grade measurement delivered in the field.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Donor Experience -->
  <section class="bg-light section-padding">
    <div class="container-narrow max-w-3xl">
      <p class="label text-primary mb-6">The Donor Experience</p>
      <h2 class="mb-8">You see exactly where your money goes.</h2>
      <p class="text-body text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Inspired by the Charity: Water model — the organization that proved donors give more when they can see the project, track the progress, and witness the outcome.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h4 class="font-serif font-bold mb-2">Choose a project</h4>
          <p class="text-body text-sm">Select a partner facility and population. Know where your dollars land.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h4 class="font-serif font-bold mb-2">Receive updates</h4>
          <p class="text-body text-sm">Progress reports as the deployment moves from funded to active to complete.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h4 class="font-serif font-bold mb-2">See outcomes</h4>
          <p class="text-body text-sm">Real numbers from real sessions. Symptom reduction. Recovery rates. Stories.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Partner Requirements -->
  <section class="bg-white section-padding">
    <div class="container-narrow max-w-3xl">
      <p class="label text-primary mb-6">For Partners</p>
      <h2 class="mb-8">What we look for in a partner facility.</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-gold font-bold text-xl mt-1">1</span>
          <p class="text-body"><strong>Established organization</strong> — currently serving trauma-affected populations with existing infrastructure and staff.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-gold font-bold text-xl mt-1">2</span>
          <p class="text-body"><strong>On-site delivery model</strong> — a physical location where sessions can be administered regularly (residential preferred).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-gold font-bold text-xl mt-1">3</span>
          <p class="text-body"><strong>Willing to train</strong> — at least one staff member committed to learning and administering sessions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-gold font-bold text-xl mt-1">4</span>
          <p class="text-body"><strong>Commitment to measurement</strong> — willingness to track outcomes and report data for donor transparency.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-deep text-white section-padding text-center">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 class="text-white text-3xl mb-6">Fund the next deployment.</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/give" class="btn-gold text-lg">Give now</a>
        <a href="/partners" class="btn-primary text-lg">Become a partner</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
